# One base64-encoded Noise XK static public key per line.
#
# Lines beginning with `#` and blank lines are ignored.
#
# To get a client key, run on the client machine after `veil connect`
# has been started once: the binary creates a fresh keypair on first
# run, prints the public key on the first log line, and persists the
# private side in the configured `static_key_path`.
#
# Example (do NOT use this; it is a placeholder):
# AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA=
